div.p:
Luther the Founder of this fifth Gospel geueth this Censure of you, and of your felowes of Peter Martyrs,Tom. 2. Fol. 263.
       and Caluines schoole. Frustra illi in Deum patrem, & filium, & Spiritum sanctum credunt. omnia (inquam) haec nihil illis prosunt, quando hunc Articulum negant, eum{que}


falsi insimulant, qui de Sacramento dixit, Hoc est corpus meum. They beleeue in God the Father, and in the Sonne, and in the Holy Ghoste in vaine. Al these thinges (say I) profite them nothing, forasmuche as they denye this Article (he meaneth the Article of Christes real Presence in the Sacrament) and make him a false reporter, who said of the Sacrament, This is my Body.
